Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the potatoes.

Chop the @Potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat.

Add a knob of @Butter{knob} and a splash of @Water{splash} or @?Milk{splash}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}. Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, place a hand flat on top of the @Irish Chicken Breast{320%grams} and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Repeat with the other breast(s).

Season the chicken with salt and pepper.

Wrap the @Irish Bacon{170%grams} slices around the chicken steaks.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

== Honeyed Carrots ==

Trim the @Carrot{2}(trimmed and halved lengthways) and cut into 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

On a lined #baking tray{} toss with salt, pepper and a drizzle of @Oil{drizzle}.

Roast on the middle shelf of the oven until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Once cooked, toss the roasted carrots with the @Honey{1%sachet}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Chicken al Forno ==

Place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, lay in the chicken, with the bacon facing seam-side down.

Cook until golden brown and crispy, ~{4-8%minutes} on each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to an #ovenproof dish{}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with the garlic and a drizzle of oil. Fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Passata{1%pack}, @Chicken Stock{1%sachet}, @Worcester Sauce{1%sachet} and @Sugar{1/4%tsp}. Bring to the boil.

Simmer until thickened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Taste and add salt and pepper if needed.

Pour the sauce over the chicken, then drain, tear and scatter the @Mozzarella{125%grams} over the top.

Bake the chicken on the top shelf of the oven until cheese is melted, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Share your bacon wrapped chicken between plates.

Serve creamy mash and honeyed carrots.

Spoon over any remaining sauce to finish.